{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_018bN4RwaLFzekPgZUdjyeoy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah! Here's the problem! The CHAR_IN_CLASS macro is:\n```c\n#define CHAR_IN_CLASS(cls, chr)  \\\n  ((cls)[(chr) / 8] & 1 << ((chr) % 8))\n```\n\nThis calculates which bit in which byte of the bitmap represents the character.\n\nFor a character value of 224 (0xE0):\n- If it's treated as unsigned: 224 / 8 = 28, 224 % 8 = 0\n- If it's treated as signed char (-32): -32 / 8 = -4, -32 % 8 = -4 (or 4 depending on the language/implementation)\n\nIf chr is negative, then (chr) / 8 could be negative, which would cause an array out-of-bounds access to the bitmap!\n\nThis is the bug! When yr_altercase[chr] is used where chr = 224 (0xE0):\n1. yr_altercase[224] should return 224 (since 224 is not a letter)\n2. But yr_altercase is now declared as `char` (signed)\n3. The value 224 when stored in a signed char becomes -32\n4. So yr_altercase[224] returns -32\n5. When this -32 is used in CHAR_IN_CLASS macro as `chr`, it calculates (-32) / 8 = -4\n6. The bitmap has a limited size, so accessing bitmap[-4] is likely reading from outside the bitmap!\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-check the re.c code. The call is:\n```c\nresult |= CHAR_IN_CLASS(re_class->bitmap, yr_altercase[chr]);\n```\n\nWhere chr is an unsigned char (the input byte). So:\n\n\n- chr = 224 (0xE0, unsigned)\n- yr_altercase[224] returns -32 when read as a signed char\n\nWhen this signed value gets passed to the macro, it's used directly in the division and modulo operations. The negative index causes an out-of-bounds access into the bitmap, corrupting the character class lookup.\n\nThis explains why bytes above 127 fail—they're being interpreted as negative numbers, breaking the indexing scheme that assumes non-negative values.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":472,"cache_read_input_tokens":49830,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":472},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b5bc1dc-71cc-41aa-984b-77d6fdcad658","uuid":"7fb730f9-a4c6-48fd-a529-52619a7c2fcb"}
