{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_011Cg6VqJz1SgqSjYhCt1Vo8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! This confirms the issue. When yr_altercase[224] is a signed char, it returns -32, and when this is used in the CHAR_IN_CLASS macro for bitmap operations:\n- `(-32) / 8 = -4` (accessing bitmap at negative index - undefined behavior)\n- vs. the correct `224 / 8 = 28`\n\nThis breaks character class matching for case-insensitive regex patterns when the input contains bytes > 127.\n\nNow I have all the information needed for my final answer:\n1. Root cause: Changed from uint8_t to char, causing sign extension\n2. Local fix: Change char back to uint8_t in both declarations\n3. Global fix: Add type safety checks or use proper unsigned types from the start","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":866,"cache_read_input_tokens":53960,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":866},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b5bc1dc-71cc-41aa-984b-77d6fdcad658","uuid":"7fe45095-3d3b-48a8-bf43-bcd99354a807"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_011Cg6VqJz1SgqSjYhCt1Vo8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! This confirms the issue. Now I have all the information needed.\n\n## ROOT CAUSE\n\n**File: `libyara/include/yara/globals.h:40-41` and `libyara/libyara.c:75-76`**\n\nThe arrays `yr_lowercase` and `yr_altercase` were changed from `uint8_t` to `char` (signed). This causes sign extension for byte values > 127. \n\nWhen processing the regex `/abc([^\\\"\\\\\\\\])*\\\"/` with `nocase` flag on input `\"abc\\xE0\\x22\"`:\n1. The byte 0xE0 (224) is read from the array as a signed char, becoming -32\n2. This negative value is then used in the `CHAR_IN_CLASS` macro: `(chr) / 8` becomes `-32 / 8 = -4`\n3. The negative index causes out-of-bounds access to the bitmap array, breaking character class matching\n4. The test case at `tests/test-rules.c:1552` fails because the regex incorrectly fails to match valid input\n\n## LOCAL FIX\n\nIn `libyara/include/yara/globals.h`, change line 40-41:\n```diff\n- extern char yr_lowercase[256];\n- extern char yr_altercase[256];\n+ extern uint8_t yr_lowercase[256];\n+ extern uint8_t yr_altercase[256];\n```\n\nIn `libyara/libyara.c`, change line 75-76:\n```diff\n- char yr_lowercase[256];\n- char yr_altercase[256];\n+ uint8_t yr_lowercase[256];\n+ uint8_t yr_altercase[256];\n```\n\nAlso restore the removed include in `libyara/include/yara/globals.h`:\n```diff\n+ #include <inttypes.h>\n```\n\n## GLOBAL FIX\n\nUse unsigned integer types (`uint8_t`, `unsigned char`) consistently for all byte-valued lookup tables and character data. This prevents sign extension bugs when byte values (0-255) are used as array indices or in bit-level operations. Add static analysis checks or type safety guidelines that flag assignments of byte data to signed `char` arrays, especially when those arrays are used in arithmetic operations that assume unsigned semantics."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":866,"cache_read_input_tokens":53960,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":866},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b5bc1dc-71cc-41aa-984b-77d6fdcad658","uuid":"e0adea98-bdc1-4571-b1f4-77347ff93c82"}
